Ticket #007 - Join Workstation to Active Directory Domain
Request

Join a new workstation to the Active Directory domain to allow centralized management and authentication.

Environment

Windows Server Active Directory Domain Controller

Domain:
lab.local

Actions Taken

Performed workstation domain join procedure:

Created a new Windows Server EC2 instance to simulate a workstation.
Configured the workstation to use the Domain Controller as its DNS server.
Verified network connectivity to the Domain Controller.
Joined the workstation to the lab.local domain.
Restarted the workstation to complete the domain join process.
Verified the workstation appeared in Active Directory Users and Computers.
Moved the workstation into the Workstations Organizational Unit.
Verification

Confirmed the workstation successfully joined the lab.local domain and appeared in the correct Organizational Unit within Active Directory.

Result

The workstation was successfully joined to the Active Directory domain and is now managed through Active Directory.

Status

Completed
